[SN]TITLE[SN]
Aldergrove: Man knocked down and seriously injured

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been seriously injured after he was knocked down by a vehicle close to Belfast International Airport.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He was walking on the Ballyrobin Road, Aldergrove, when the collision took place shortly before 16:40 GMT on Saturday.
A spokesman for the Northern Ireland Ambulance Service said the pedestrian was taken to the Royal Victoria Hospital in Belfast.
Ballyrobin Road has been closed from the airport to Tully Road roundabout.
Diversions are in place and police have advised motorists travelling to the airport to leave extra time for their journey.
